{"title_page": "Zororo Makamba", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean journalist}}\n{{Notability|Biographies|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Zororo Makamba\n| image         = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1990|01|17}}\n| birth_place   = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2020|03|23|1990|01|17}} \n| death_place   = Harare, Zimbabwe \n| death_cause   = [[COVID-19]]\n| nationality   = Zimbabwean\n| father        = [[James Makamba]]  \n| mother        = Irene Makamba\n| alma_mater    = \n| occupation    = Journalist\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| website       = {{url|zororomakamba.com/}}\n}}\n'''Zororo Makamba''' (17 January 1990 \u2013 23 March 2020) was a Zimbabwean journalist and the son of Irene and [[James Makamba]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Roberts|first=Sam|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/30/obituaries/zororo-makamba-30-dies-zimbabwean-television-host.html|title=Zororo Makamba, 30, Dies; Zimbabwean Television Host|date=2020-03-30|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nMakamba posted commentary on Zimbabwean politics and society online under the heading \"State of the Nation\",<ref name=BBC>{{cite news |first=Shingai |last=Nyoka |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-52061697 |title=Coronavirus: Zimbabwean broadcaster Zororo Makamba died 'alone and scared' |publisher=BBC News |date=28 March 2020 }}</ref> and hosted current affairs programs on [[ZiFM Stereo]] and [[M-Net]] television affiliate Zambezi Magic.\n\nHe had [[myasthenia gravis]], a neuroskeletomuscular autoimmune disease, and underwent surgery to remove a chest tumor in November 2019. He was diagnosed on 21 March 2020 with [[COVID-19]], twelve days after returning from [[New York City]] and five days after going to a doctor with a cough and fever. He died in [[Harare]] two days later, the first infected death in the country.<ref name=BBC/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/journalist-zororo-makamba-becomes-zimbabwes-first-covid-19-death-20200323|title=Journalist Zororo Makamba becomes Zimbabwe's first Covid-19 death|last=Maphanga|first=Canny|date=2020-03-23|website=News24|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/africa/2020-03-23-journalist-is-first-person-in-zimbabwe-to-die-from-covid-19/|title=Journalist is first person in Zimbabwe to die from Covid-19|website=TimesLIVE|language=en-ZA|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/africa/media-personality-zororo-makamba-becomes-first-zimbabwe-coronavirus-fatality-45410008|title=Media personality Zororo Makamba becomes first Zimbabwe coronavirus fatality|last=Daniels|first=Lou-Anne|date=23 March 2020|website=www.iol.co.za|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Zimbabwe]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Makamba, Zororo}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean journalists]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Zimbabwe]]\n[[Category:Infectious disease deaths in Zimbabwe]]\n[[Category:21st-century journalists]]\n\n\n{{Zimbabwe-bio-stub}}\n{{Africa-journalist-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Zimbabwean journalist}}\n{{Notability|Biographies|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Zororo Makamba\n| image         = \n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = \n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|1990|01|17}}\n| birth_place   = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|2020|03|23|1990|01|17}} \n| death_place   = Harare, Zimbabwe \n| death_cause   = [[COVID-19]]\n| nationality   = Zimbabwean\n| father        = [[James Makamba]]  \n| mother        = Irene Makamba\n| alma_mater    = \n| occupation    = Journalist\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = \n| notable_works = \n| website       = {{url|zororomakamba.com/}}\n}}\n'''Zororo Makamba''' (17 January 1990 \u2013 23 March 2020) was a Zimbabwean journalist and the son of Irene and [[James Makamba]]<ref>{{Cite news|last=Roberts|first=Sam|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/30/obituaries/zororo-makamba-30-dies-zimbabwean-television-host.html|title=Zororo Makamba, 30, Dies; Zimbabwean Television Host|date=2020-03-30|work=The New York Times|access-date=2020-04-12|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>.\n==Biography==\nMakamba posted commentary on Zimbabwean politics and society online under the heading \"State of the Nation\",<ref name=BBC>{{cite news |first=Shingai |last=Nyoka |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-52061697 |title=Coronavirus: Zimbabwean broadcaster Zororo Makamba died 'alone and scared' |publisher=BBC News |date=28 March 2020 }}</ref> and hosted current affairs programs on [[ZiFM Stereo]] and [[M-Net]] television affiliate Zambezi Magic. \n\nHe had [[myasthenia gravis]], a neuroskeletomuscular autoimmune disease, and underwent surgery to remove a chest tumor in November 2019. He was diagnosed on 21 March 2020 with [[COVID-19]], twelve days after returning from [[New York City]] and five days after going to a doctor with a cough and fever. He died in [[Harare]] two days later, the first infected death in the country.<ref name=BBC/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/journalist-zororo-makamba-becomes-zimbabwes-first-covid-19-death-20200323|title=Journalist Zororo Makamba becomes Zimbabwe's first Covid-19 death|last=Maphanga|first=Canny|date=2020-03-23|website=News24|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/news/africa/2020-03-23-journalist-is-first-person-in-zimbabwe-to-die-from-covid-19/|title=Journalist is first person in Zimbabwe to die from Covid-19|website=TimesLIVE|language=en-ZA|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/africa/media-personality-zororo-makamba-becomes-first-zimbabwe-coronavirus-fatality-45410008|title=Media personality Zororo Makamba becomes first Zimbabwe coronavirus fatality|last=Daniels|first=Lou-Anne|date=23 March 2020|website=www.iol.co.za|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Zimbabwe]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Makamba, Zororo}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean journalists]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Zimbabwe]]\n[[Category:Infectious disease deaths in Zimbabwe]]\n[[Category:21st-century journalists]]\n\n\n{{Zimbabwe-bio-stub}}\n{{Africa-journalist-stub}}\n{{COVID-19-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zororo_Makamba"}
